(42, 14, 13, 18, 31, 16, 20, 'the poor', 'Connection of Caring for the Poor', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of caring for the poor and marginalized. Luke 14:13 instructs to invite the poor, while Job 31:16-20 reflects on the consequences of neglecting their needs.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 13, 58, 13, 2, 2, 'call the poor, the maimed, the lame, the blind', 'Hospitality and Care for Others', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of caring for those in need, whether the poor and disabled in Luke or strangers in Hebrews. This connection highlights a theme of hospitality and kindness towards marginalized individuals.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 14, 20, 19, 17, 17, 'thou shalt be recompensed', 'Blessings for Helping the Poor', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being rewarded for acts of kindness, particularly towards those in need. Luke 14:14 speaks of recompense at the resurrection, while Proverbs 19:17 highlights that lending to the poor is like lending to the Lord, promising repayment.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 14, 44, 24, 15, 15, 'recompensed at the resurrection of the just', 'Resurrection of the Just', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of resurrection, specifically mentioning the ''just'' in relation to their ultimate recompense. Luke highlights the blessing of being recompensed at the resurrection, while Acts speaks to the resurrection of both the just and unjust.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 14, 43, 5, 29, 29, 'recompensed at the resurrection of the just', 'Resurrection of the Just', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection in both passages. Luke 14:14 speaks of recompense at the resurrection of the just, while John 5:29 distinguishes between the resurrection of life for the good and damnation for the evil.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
